Then $\triangle ABE$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so $AE = 2AB.$  Also, $\triangle CDE$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so $CE = 2CD.$  Hence,
\[\frac{AD}{BC} = \frac{AE - DE}{CE} = \frac{2AB - 2CD}{2CD} = \frac{AB - CD}{CD}.\]Since $AB = CD,$ $\frac{AD}{BC} = \boxed{0}.$

We draw a perpendicular from $D$ to $BC$ as shown: [asy]
