[/asy] Since $\triangle BCD$ is equilateral, $BD=CD$. Also, $\triangle ABD$ and $\triangle ACD$ are congruent 30-60-90 triangles, so $AD=2BD$. Thus $BC+BD=BC+CD=BC+AD/2=AD/2+AD/2=AD$. Using the Pythagorean Theorem on $\triangle BDE$, we get \begin{align*}
DE^2+BD^2&=BE^2\\
\left(\frac{BC}{2}\right)^2+BD^2&=BC^2\\
\frac{BC^2}{4}+BD^2&=BC^2\\
BD^2&=\frac{3}{4}BC^2.
\end{align*}Thus, $AD=BC+BD=BC+\sqrt{\frac{3}{4}}BC=\frac{BC(2+\sqrt{3})}{2}$, so $AD\div BC=\boxed{\frac{2+\sqrt{3}}{2}}$.

