\[\frac{AP}{AB} = \frac{AD}{AQ}.\]Since $AB = AD = s$, this becomes
\[\frac{AP}{s} = \frac{s}{AQ}.\]Then $AP \cdot AQ = s^2 = 6$.  Also, $AP + AQ = s$, so $AQ = s - AP$.  Substituting, we get
