The side length of the square is $BC=1$.  The area of the octagon is equal to the area of the square $BDEF$ minus the four congruent right isosceles triangles with legs $BF=DE=1$.

The area of the square is $(BC)^2=1^2=1$, and the area of one of the triangles is $\frac{1^2}{2}= \frac{1}{2}$, so the area of all four triangles is $4\cdot \frac{1}{2}=2$.  Therefore, the area of the octagon is $1-2=\boxed{\frac{1}{2}}$.

The area of the square is $(BC)^2 = 1.$

